<paragraph id="73DFA06607FCC5C07E58139751602FDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="A99EE1A7C660868209301861F73133D2" LSID="B7799DF9-6A60-5E8F-BAAA-D544A465F042" authority="M. Sars, 1851" authorityName="M. Sars" authorityYear="1851" class="Polychaeta" family="Capitellidae" genus="Notomastus" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notomastus" order="Capitellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">Notomastus M. Sars, 1851</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="61807746B253236896FF4A01B44E6B55" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="type species">
<paragraph id="2074FB73E207B6DF192133CEA9640C8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="380BA1A9D4618DE598F55FC5A9BF3AFE" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName id="4BCF2A2B0DD84829D5348BB97A18C1A1" authorityName="Sars" authorityYear="1851" class="Polychaeta" family="Capitellidae" genus="Notomastus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notomastus latericeus" order="Capitellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="latericeus">
<emphasis id="F12E53A5381A49668A87350222EDAE0C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notomastus latericeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
M. Sars, 1851: 199-200.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EE9C0DF29AE4593559C92391325AB1F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9AF159B68BF11EE11354A992B9F49F59" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA01DA83F5A920A951BA35BCEC2A86DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="948B8D55F6D41A51D5F78B0D3DF53F31" authorityName="M. Sars" authorityYear="1851" class="Polychaeta" family="Capitellidae" genus="Notomastus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Notomastus" order="Capitellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="72DDDADDD7A10521A110387A1F1D4AB4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notomastus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a conical prostomium, palpode present or absent; eyespots present in multiple spots or absent. Peristomium clearly distinct from prostomium. First chaetiger uniramous or biramous. Eleven thoracic chaetigers. Chaetigers 1-11 with only capillaries or last 1-3 thoracic chaetigers with notopodial capillaries and neuropodial hooks. Abdominal segments with only hooded hooks. Branchiae present or lacking. Genital pores present or absent. Lateral organs present on thorax and abdomen. Pygidium unadorned but unknown for many species (
<bibRefCitation id="E4689790AC09CFF7C5AECFFE482F26A8" author="Magalhaes, WF" editor="Westheide, W" journalOrPublisher="De Gruyter, Boston / Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 49" publicationUrl="www.degruyter.com/view/zoology/bp_029147-6_76" refId="B23" refString="Magalhaes, WF, Blake, JA, 2019. Capitellidae Grube, 1862. In: Westheide, W, Purschke, G, Boeggemann, M, Eds., Handbook of Zoology Online, a Natural History of the Phyla of the Animal Kingdom, Annelida: Polychaetes. De Gruyter, Boston/Berlin: 1 - 49, www.degruyter.com/view/zoology/bp_029147-6_76" title="Capitellidae Grube, 1862." url="www.degruyter.com/view/zoology/bp_029147-6_76" volumeTitle="Handbook of Zoology Online, a Natural History of the Phyla of the Animal Kingdom, Annelida: Polychaetes." year="2019">
<normalizedToken id="DEF05A01F9683F20821FA30C53D3CF35" originalValue="Magalhães">Magalhaes</normalizedToken>
and Blake 2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
